2.00	Shartlesville,_Pennsylvania	Shartlesville, Pennsylvania	Shartlesville, Pennsylvania is a small unincorporated community in Upper Bern Township, located in upper Berks County. It is located just south of Interstate 78 and is served by the Hamburg Area School District. It is home to the Shartlesville Hotel, which suffered major roof damage in February 2009 during a wind storm, which also knocked down a billboard in Reading and blew off roof tiles of the Pagoda in eastern Reading.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fb/Map_of_Pennsylvania_highlighting_Berks_County.svg/180px-Map_of_Pennsylvania_highlighting_Berks_County.svg.png
